Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring flight attendants.
2 Whereas, There are 130,800 flight attendants in the United
3 States;
4 Whereas, Flight attendants are essential to passenger
5 aviation, demonstrate bravery, knowledge, and stoicism in
6 emergencies, and are a first line of defense against bad actors;
7 Whereas, Flight attendants are dedicated to safety
8 procedures, including evacuations and disruptive passengers,
9 and passenger service;
10 Whereas, Air travel is increasing, with passengers expected
11 to double by 2043 according to the International Air Transport
12 Association;
13
14 Whereas, It is a longstanding practice that flight attendants
15 are not paid for work performed during boarding and de-
16 boarding; and
17 Whereas, Boarding and de-boarding time can amount to
18 four hours a day of unpaid work for flight attendants;
2026 DR 3836/DI aj

2
1 Therefore:
2
3 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
4 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
5
6 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors flight
7 attendants for their service.
8
9 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is directed to
10 transmit copies of this Resolution to Dustin Roach.
2026 DR 3836/DI aj

